My Meme

This meme depicts Winnie’s varying reactions to programming language. The idea for this meme is from my programming experience. You can do anything effortlessly with the help of CHATGPT (not recommend cheating tho).

library(magick)

# Square no.1

red_winnie <- image_read('https://uploads.dailydot.com/2019/04/winnie-the-pooh.jpg?auto=compress&fm=pjpg') %>%
  image_scale(500)

# Square no.2 text

square2_text = image_blank(width=150,
                           height=50,
                           color = "black") %>%
  image_annotate(text = 'Python', 
                 color='white',
                 size = 25, 
                 font = 'Impact', 
                 gravity = "center")


# Square no.2 photo

square2_photo <- image_read('https://images.hdqwalls.com/wallpapers/python-logo-4k-i6.jpg') %>%
  image_scale(150)

# Square no.2 vector

square2_vector <- c(square2_text, square2_photo) %>% 
  image_append(stack = TRUE)%>% 
  image_scale(280)

# Top_row
top_vector <-c(red_winnie,square2_vector)

top_row <- image_append(top_vector) %>% 
  image_scale(400)

# Square no.3
black_winnie <- image_read('https://uproxx.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/tuxedopooh.jpg') %>%
  image_scale(500)

# Square no.4 text
square4_text = image_blank(width=150,
                           height=50,
                           color = "black") %>%
  image_annotate(text = 'R', 
                 color= 'white',
                 size = 25, 
                 font = 'Impact', 
                 gravity = "center")

# Square no.4 photo
square4_photo <- image_read('https://miro.medium.com/max/1400/1*-8muILFEhglD5wXw-7nWag.png') %>%
  image_scale(150)

# Square no.4 vector

square4_vector <- c(square4_text, square4_photo) %>% 
  image_append(stack = TRUE)%>% 
  image_scale(345)

# Second_row
second_vector <-c(black_winnie,square4_vector)

second_row <- image_append(second_vector) %>% 
  image_scale(400)

# Square no.5 
ugly_winnie <- image_read('https://i.kym-cdn.com/editorials/icons/mobile/000/000/705/derp.jpg') %>%
  image_scale(500)

# Square no.6 text
square6_text = image_blank(width=150,
                           height=50,
                           color = "black") %>%
  image_annotate(text = 'CHATGPT', 
                 color= 'white',
                 size = 25, 
                 font = 'Impact', 
                 gravity = "center")

# Square no.6 photo
square6_photo <- image_read('https://images.indianexpress.com/2023/01/chatgpt-extension.jpg') %>%
  image_scale(150)

# Square no.6 vector

square6_vector <- c(square6_text, square6_photo) %>% 
  image_append(stack = TRUE) %>% 
  image_scale(318)

# Third_row
Third_vector <-c(ugly_winnie,square6_vector)

Third_row <- image_append(Third_vector) %>% 
  image_scale(400)

meme <- c(top_row, second_row, Third_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE) %>%
  image_scale(1000)

meme %>% image_write("my_meme.png")

My animated GIF

This meme is about Wojak programming with the help of ChatGPT. The inspiration is from my personal’s experience (I was working on Python-based side project and use ChatGPT for assistance, resulting in extensive debugging works.)

library(magick)

# Frame1 picture
frame_1 <- image_read('https://i.kym-cdn.com/entries/icons/original/000/018/433/wojak.jpg') %>% 
  image_annotate(text = 'When you asked to program', 
                 gravity = 'east', 
                 size = 35, 
                 font = 'Impact') %>% 
  image_scale(680)

# Frame2 picture
frame_2 <- image_read('https://www.goalcast.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Untitled-design-48.jpg') %>%
  image_annotate(text='But you realized you know nothing about programming', 
                 gravity = 'northwest', 
                 size = 40, 
                 font = 'Impact') %>%
  image_scale(700)

# Frame3 picture
frame_3_big_brain <- image_read('https://i.imgflip.com/52ru6j.png') %>%
  image_annotate(text='But you \n remember \n you can \n use CHATGPT', 
                 gravity = 'East', 
                 size = 40, 
                 font = 'Impact') %>%
  image_scale(800)

frame3_chatGPT <- image_read('https://i0.wp.com/technewsspace.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Microsoft-allows-third-parties-to-create-their-own-versions-of.jpg') %>%
  image_scale(500)

frame3_vector <- c(frame_3_big_brain, frame3_chatGPT) 

frame_3 <- image_append(frame3_vector) %>%
  image_scale(700)

# Frame4 picture
frame_4 <- image_read('https://i.pinimg.com/736x/29/d0/9b/29d09b463db7ef73c8d636abeae94565.jpg') %>%
  image_annotate(text = 'And you did the entire program in 5 mins', 
                 gravity = 'North', 
                 size = 33, 
                 font = 'Impact') %>%
  image_scale(450)

# Frame5 picture
frame_5_shocking <- image_read('https://i.imgur.com/oh32lCh.jpeg') 

frame_5_text <- image_blank(width=500,
                            height=100,
                            color = "white") %>%
  image_annotate(text = 'And then this pop up', 
                 color='black',
                 size = 45, 
                 font = 'Impact', 
                 gravity = "center")

frame_5_error <- image_read('https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/22758616/35866204-d2ec0c5c-0b56-11e8-8f21-d993eaac86a1.PNG') 

frame_5_vector <- c(frame_5_text,frame_5_error) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE) %>% 
  image_scale(400)

frame_5_vector_2 <- c(frame_5_shocking,frame_5_vector)

frame_5 <- image_append(frame_5_vector_2) %>% 
  image_scale(700)

# Frame6 picture
frame_6 <- image_read('https://i.imgflip.com/4u8tgt.jpg') %>% 
  image_annotate(text = 'You eventually spent 5 hours re-writing \n the entire code and debugging', 
                 color = 'black', 
                 gravity = 'North', 
                 size = '30', 
                 font = 'impact') %>%
  image_scale(450)


# Output
frames <- c(frame_1,frame_2,frame_3,frame_4,frame_5, frame_6)

animation <- image_animate(frames, fps=0.5)

image_write(animation, "my_animation.gif")
